    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">195.1/15½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                        Counselor for the Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lansing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: Surely if Mr. Morgan’s
                    information is correct as stated in the enclosed letter,<note n="1a"
                        xml:id="d91fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> the British Government is in danger of
                    taking a very unjustifiable and high-handed action. I would very much like your
                    carefully considered opinion on the subject.</p>
                <p>Cordially yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
